Product Version     25.10    Cadence Design Systems, Inc.
set_multi_input_switching_mode(25.10)    set_multi_input_switching_mode(25.10)

Name
       set_multi_input_switching_mode - Configures multi-input switching (MIS)
       mode settings

Syntax
       set_multi_input_switching_mode

       [-help]

       [-disable_lib_cells <<string>>]

       [-mis_alignment_mode {0 | 1}]

       [-switching_alignment_factor <<float>>]

        [-view <string>]

       Configures multi-input switching (MIS) mode settings.

       You  can  enable  the  MIS feature using the setAnalysisMode -multi_in-
       put_switching_mode command parameter.

       For reporting advanced MIS in delay calculation and delta delay in tim-
       ing reports, you can use the following options:

              *

                * report_delay_calculation -mis

                * report_timing -format retime_mis_delta

                * report_timing_format {retime_mis_delta}

Parameters
       -help  Prints out the command usage.

       -disable_lib_cells <string>
              Enables or disables the multi-input switching (MIS) mode support
              for the specified library cells.

              Default: " "

       -mis_alignment_mode {0 | 1}
              Controls the MIS alignment mode.

              Default: 0

       -switching_alignment_factor <<float>>
              Allows to  configure  the  relative  alignment  of  side  inputs
              switching  with  respect  to  the  primary inputs. The switching
              alignment factor is applied for all the instances for which  MIS
              analysis is to be performed.

              This  parameter  accepts  values  between -1 to 1. These are de-
              scribed below:

              * 1: Side inputs switch at the earliest arrival.

              * 0: Side inputs switch at the same time as actual input.

              * -1: All the side inputs switch at the same time and  align  at
                the completion of the output pin transition.

              Default: 0

              Note:  Setting  the -switching_alignment_factor to 1 can be pes-
              simistic if a side input switches much earlier than the main in-
              put. You can use the  -mis_alignment_mode  parameter  to  reduce
              pessimism in this mode.

       -view <<string>>
              Specifies the name of the view.

Examples
              * The  following  commands disable MIS support for the specified
                library cells:

                set_multi_input_switching_mode              -disable_lib_cells
                [get_libs_cell aoi*]

                set_multi_input_switching_mode              -disable_lib_cells
                [get_libs_cell lib_0.510v/aoi*]

